Patch Set 1:

I checked neutron/keystone code and both are providing support for running --expand, --migrate, --contrast optionally, while glance is running all three implicitly: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/433934/15/glance/cmd/manage.py@119.
I think this should be optionally done when doing upgrade and should not change the default behaviour of db_sync. Adding warning is Ok as it is required when running --expand.

Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

Technically this solution seems fine. My only concern is making sure we're clear about documenting the behavior. I don't thin the piece of doc change included in this change is exactly related to the change and should be here, but I do think we need to clarify thing or two.

Looking the documentation it's not obvious to me that the db_sync is meant for offline usage, specially after the f268df1c merged and made the statement that it's using EMC under the hood anyways.

Could we please move that rolling upgrades doc change to it's own and document a bug that we need to improve the documentation around this? I'd be more than happy to approve this change so we get to test it in case of we need to revisit it once more before release.
Patch Set 5: Published edit on patch set 4.
Patch Set 5: Code-Review+1

Patch Set 5:

The E-M-C strategy is to split a database migration into three stages, whereas we previously had monolithic migrations.  Splitting them this way allows the possibility of "live" DB upgrades (which we support only for MySQL because of the triggers).  The "offline" migration uses the E-M-C strategy so that we don't have to maintain separate online vs. offline scripts.  But you are right that we need more documentation around this.
